                                        </p>

                                        <!-- FAQ Section -->
                                        <h3 class="mt-4">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h3>
                                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush text-left">
                                        <li class="list-group-item bg-transparent">
                                            <strong>How can I donate items?</strong>
                                            <p>Click the "Send Help" option in the News Feed section, select the items you wish to donate, and specify the recipient. Your items will then be matched with those in need.</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li class="list-group-item bg-transparent">
                                            <strong>How can I request help?</strong>
                                            <p>In the "Request Help" section, specify the items or services you need, such as food, clothes, or shelter. Our platform will connect you with donors who can assist.</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li class="list-group-item bg-transparent">
                                            <strong>What is the Community Risk Assessment Tool?</strong>
                                            <p>This tool helps assess disaster risks in your area, providing important data on natural disasters and preparedness so you can stay informed.</p>
                                        </li>
                                        <li class="list-group-item bg-transparent">
                                            <strong>How do I report an emergency?</strong>
                                            <p>Use the "One-Tap SOS Reporting" feature to quickly send a distress signal to our team. We will respond as soon as possible to assist you.</p>
                                        </li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

